## Mechanics

### Facility Building
- `buildFacility(cityId, facId)`
- Cost = FT[f].cost
- One facility per type per city (anti-duplicate check)
- Owner = 'player' for player-built, 'auto' for world-gen

### Facility Upgrade
- `upgradeFacility(cityId, idx)`
- Level 1→5
- Cost = cost × level × 1.8
- Efficiency +12% per level (cap 150%)
- Only player-owned facilities can be upgraded

### Auto-Generation
- Cities generate facilities at world gen based on city type
- Max facilities: village=1, town=2, city=4, metro=6
- Only tier 1-2, assigned random owner='auto'

### Production (processFacilities)
- Runs every game tick (every 3 ticks = 1 day)
- Consumes inputs from city supply
- Produces outputs to city supply
- Service facilities generate gold directly

### Service Revenue
- Inn: $8 × level × efficiency / day
- Bar: $15 × level × efficiency / day
- Bank: $30 × level × efficiency / day
- Gold goes to facility owner (player or city GDP)

### CEO Company
- `foundCompany(sector)` — requires $20K
- Sector selection modal with 10 options:
  - 5 production (agri, mine, manu, ener, svc)
  - 5 business (finance, tech, military, logistics, general)
- Company expansion: $5K + 1% of city pop per city
- IPO: $50K to go public
- Hostile takeover: 51% ownership required

## UI

### City Modal
- Facilities section with build/upgrade UI
- Shows existing facilities with level bars (■■■□□)
- "Build New" section grouped by sector
- Upgrade button shows cost, hidden at max level

### Finance Modal
- Player-owned facilities with revenue/day display
- Per-city grouping

### Tech Tree Modal (🔬)
- All 13 facilities organized by sector
- Tier indicators, inputs→outputs chain
- Service revenue chart
- Accessed via HUD button

### Found Company Modal
- Sector selector with description cards
- 10 sectors, cost display
- Called from city "Found Co" button

## Implementation
- Functions: buildFacility, upgradeFacility, foundCompany(sector), mdTechTree, mdFoundCompany
- Patches: 16 (v5.6.0)
- Lines: ~105 added
